{
  // Probe on §22.8 / §10.2: "Public requests and engine maintenance run without
  // an actor" and "A public operation has no `$actor` or `$session`." The spec
  // says a public request has no `$actor`, but does NOT pin what happens when a
  // public mutation *references* `$actor`. Three readings are each grounded in
  // spec text, and SPEC.md chooses none:
  //   (a) static rejection at load — §6.2: structural bindings (incl. `$actor`)
  //       "exist only in the feature context that defines them" (authentication),
  //       so referencing it from a public mutation could be an invalid package;
  //   (b) runtime rejection at admission — §6.3: a `$actor` context "MUST
  //       receive exactly one occurrence. Zero … reject that evaluation"; with
  //       no actor bound the reference has zero occurrences and the request
  //       fails at admission;
  //   (c) a null/absent binding written through to the optional field.
  // The behavior is unspecified; the corpus records the gap.
  format: 1
  name: public-request-references-actor-unspecified
  suite: scenario
  spec: ["#runtime", "§22.8", "§10.2", "§6.2", "§6.3"]
  tags: ["authz", "provenance", "boundary"]
  note: '''
    Pinned (SPEC-ISSUES #9). §22.8 now states that reading `$actor`/`$session`
    where no actor is bound is an error, never a none binding. Here the public
    surface reaches `$actor` through the declared model mutation `.add` (a
    mutation a role could also invoke), so the declaration stays valid and the
    read faults at admission as an unbound structural read (§6.3), rejecting this
    one anonymous request. A null/absent binding is never produced.
  '''

  package: {
    $liasse: 1
    $app: "t.pubactor@1.0.0"
    $model: {
      notes: {
        $key: "id"
        id: "uuid = uuid()"
        author: "text?"
        body: "text"
      }
      $mut: {
        // References $actor even though this is reached via a public surface.
        add: [
          "n = .notes + { author: $actor, body: @body }"
          "return n { id, author, body }"
        ]
      }
      $public: {
        notes: {
          $mut: { add: ".add" }
        }
      }
    }
  }

  steps: [
    { connect: "c1" }
    {
      call: "public.notes.add"
      args: { body: "who am i" }
      on: "c1"
      // Reaches $actor through the declared mutation `.add`; with no actor bound
      // the read faults at admission as an unbound structural, rejecting this
      // request (§22.8, §6.3).
      expect: { outcome: rejected, violates: ["#runtime", "§22.8", "#expressions", "§6.3"] }
    }
  ]
}
